<P>
   HISTORIC (PRESCOTT VALLEY, Ariz.) {ndash} Prescott Valley, the
fastest growing place in Arizona outside the Phoenix area, has a
huge advantage when it comes to urban planning. There was so little
there that the town never had a true downtown area. So now, the
town is about to convert 1 square mile of open space into what
community leaders predict will be one of the nation's best downtown
areas using the talents of country's top urban planners and
architects. By MARK SHAFFER. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL;
