<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Trace your family history
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   www.geocities.com/EnchantedForest/5283/genekids.htm _ Ever
wonder where you came from? This site offers kids an introduction
to tracing family roots and filling in the family tree. The
step-by-step guide takes a youngster from his or her parents' names
to the courthouse, library and church in search of the stories of
long-dead ancestors. The site includes links to several useful
research sites with vast searchable indexes. Learning about family
history can provide a good summertime family activity and a
positive introduction to history.
</P>
<P>
   cowboybobs.homestead.com/choices.html _ Visit Cowboy Bob's ranch
for an introduction to barnyard animals, including their
identifying voices, and to sing along with familiar songs, such as
``Old McDonald Had a Farm'' and ``Itsy, Bitsy Spider.'' There's
also a page with line drawings of a bunny, kitten, puppy and lion
to print out and color with crayons.
</P>
