 &HT;    Sportswriters wanted
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _
</P>
<P>
   Myteam.com is looking for a Little League Baseball player or fan
to cover the Little League World Series in Williamsport, Pa., in
August. Just write down your best story from the Little League
season in 300 words or less, and send it to Myteam.com. You must be
14 or younger, and you must hurry! The deadline is July 31. Click
on www.myteam.com for more details.
</P>
<P>
   DEAR SIXTH-GRADERS . . .
</P>
<P>
   Are you a middle-school pro? Tell us how you made the leap from
elementary school to the preteen pressures of junior high. If
you're a rising seventh- or eighth-grader, share your advice with
incoming sixth-graders. Jot down your thoughts about friends,
popularity and schoolwork, and then mail them to News for Kids at
NFK Advice, P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302. Or e-mail them to
nfk(at)ajc.com. The deadline for submissions is 5 p.m. Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   WANT TO REVIEW MOVIES?
</P>
<P>
   News for Kids is looking for a few young film buffs who will
review movies for the paper and give us their opinions. Send us a
short paragraph explaining why you would be a good reviewer, along
with a color picture of yourself (which we can use when we print
your reviews), to NFK Movies, P.O. Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302. Be
sure to include your name, age, school, county and the grade you
are entering.
