<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Tuesday, July 25, 2000 are moving
today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   EDITORIAL-TIGER _ Tiger Woods becomes the youngest player top
win golf's four major tournaments. (The Atlanta Constitution). 8.
</P>
<P>
   GOTTLIEB-COLUMN _ Here's why TV network executives should
realize covering political conventions is important: Since
television started covering conventions, conventions have been
pivotal in presidential elections. Never since 1948 has the lead in
a presidential election clearly switched hands after the
conventions. (Gottlieb, Dayton Daily News) MOVED Saturday, July 22.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ Physical exertion has never
been high on my list of priorities. Inertia is my favored motion. I
never stand when I could be sitting, and lying down is even better.
That's why, when late last summer some unknown force urged me to
put down the book, roll my rope-plaid backside out of the Pawley's
Island hammock and get it to a gym, no one was more surprised than
I was. (Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LANE-COLUMN _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ I'm trying to pinpoint a
pivotal moment in the decline of the service economy. It's when
clerks, waiters, and counter help started telling you to ``have a
good one.'' (Lane, Daytona Beach News-Journal) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET BUDGET INFORMATION FOR SUBSCRIBERS OF THE NYT NEWS
SERVICE
</P>
<P>
   Spot news budgets move daily at 2 p.m. and 6 p.m. Eastern.
Additionally, separate features and commentary budgets move at 10
a.m., and sports and business budgets at 6 p.m. Additional updates
are possible if news developments warrant.
</P>
<P>
   All times are Eastern unless otherwise noted. If stories will
move after 8 p.m., an ETA will be given.
</P>
