<P>
   GOTTLIEB-COLUMN _ Here's why TV network executives should
realize covering political conventions is important: Since
television started covering conventions, conventions have been
pivotal in presidential elections. Never since 1948 has the lead in
a presidential election clearly switched hands after the
conventions. (Gottlieb, Dayton Daily News) MOVED Saturday, July 22.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ Physical exertion has never
been high on my list of priorities. Inertia is my favored motion. I
never stand when I could be sitting, and lying down is even better.
That's why, when late last summer some unknown force urged me to
put down the book, roll my rope-plaid backside out of the Pawley's
Island hammock and get it to a gym, no one was more surprised than
I was. (Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
