   SATELLITE SIGNALS, SILICON CHIPS MULTIPLY EARTH'S BOUNTY
</P>
<P>
   HIGHTECH-HARVEST-POPMECH _ The days of farmers sitting around
the country store swapping yarns and seat-of-the-pants predictions
for the growing season are long gone. Oh, the farmers still talk
and spin yarns, but mostly through e-mail and Internet chat
sessions. And the conversation today focuses less on creaky-bone
predictions of rain and more on precision farming, the Global
Positioning System, the reliability of precise soil samples, yield
monitors and computer interfacing problems. By Mike Fillon. (1,500
words.)
