pretty close to traditional shopping. Yes, you could (and still
can) do it all from your favorite computer chair, but the process
was really no different than doing it the old-fashioned way. You
went to the store (virtually, in this case), found what you wanted,
checked the price and made the purchase. But a lot has changed.
Here's how. By Kim Komando. (1,200 words.)
