</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Despite all the pledges about
government cost-cutting and returning federal funds to the
taxpayers, members of Congress are graciously willing to make one
exception to their stingy mood: themselves. The House quietly gave
itself a $3,800 pay raise last week. In the past such
self-aggrandizement has prompted a public outcry, but now lawmakers
think the voters are so contented they won't mind. Have times
really changed that much? By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
