<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DICAPRIO FLOPS; ALMODOVAR DEMONSTRATES HIS MASTERY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``The Beach'' _ Leonardo DiCaprio's career hit the
sand like a disoriented whale in this bloated mix of mystery and
sex. Maybe he should stay out of the sea and sun for a while; he's
in danger of sinking faster than the Titanic.
</P>
<P>
   ``All About My Mother'' _ Spanish director Pedro Almodovar's
mastery of the medium can't be denied. He has one particular shot
in this melodramatic tale of Oedipal desire that's as good as
anything you'll ever see on-screen. The winner of the Academy Award
for best picture in a foreign language has English subtitles.
</P>
<P>
   ``Deuce Bigalow: Male Gigolo'' _ When a comedy lowers the bar as
low as this one and still isn't funny, you know there's trouble.
Rob Schneider makes you pray for the return of the brazen
mediocrity of Adam Sandler.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mansfield Park'' _ Director Patricia Rozema transforms the
grace and artistic innuendo of novelist Jane Austen into a
cinematic screed marked by bland performances from Frances O'Connor
and playwright Harold Pinter.
</P>
<P>
   ``Beethoven's 3rd'' _ You didn't miss this one in the theaters;
it just never opened. Judge Reinhold, whose career has spiraled
downhill ever since ``Home Alone,'' stars in the direct-to-video
installment of the St. Bernard series. It's a real bow-wow.
</P>
<P>
   ``Moon Over Broadway'' _ Those fans who saw the pre-Broadway
Boston run of Ken Ludwig's play ``Moon Over Buffalo'' might get a
real kick out of this 1998 documentary produced and directed by D.
A. Pennebaker and Chris Hegedus. It's a great idea, and the play's
stars, Philip Bosco and Carol Burnett, granted the filmmakers full
access. The DVD includes additional forthright commentary from the
principals, explaining why the play ultimately failed. The
filmmakers capture some backstage fireworks, but, given the
volatile personalities and the play's problems, the
behind-the-scenes battling might have been more explosive than what
we see.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Aug. 1: ``The Brothers Quay Collection''
(DVD). Aug. 8: ``Reindeer Games,'' ``Holy Smoke,'' ``The
Grandfather.'' Aug. 15: ``It's the Rage,'' ``Ghost Dog'' (DVD).
Aug. 22: ``The Tigger Movie'' (DVD), ``Mifune.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
