<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MORSE-COLUMN-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TOO MUCH OF A `CHICK THING' 
</HEADLINE>
   Commentary  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By ROB MORSE  
 c.2000 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ My brother was telling me about a friend of his
who bought one of the first of those new Volkswagen beetles. After
a few months tooling around in the car, he decided to sell it.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a good car,'' he said, ``but it's a chick car.''
</P>
<P>
   My brother and I both laughed, even though he's a macho guy who
lives in Cleveland and I'm a pseudo-sensitive guy from San
Francisco.
</P>
<P>
   We share an understanding of ``chick'' vs. ``guy,'' an American
cultural distinction greater than Republican vs. Democrat, highbrow
vs. lowbrow or sports utility vehicle vs. minivan.
</P>
<P>
   After all, both minivans and SUVs are chick cars, the SUV being
``the new station wagon,'' as Dave Barry once put it.
</P>
<P>
   Sorry, all you pseudo-macho guys in Land Rovers. You'll just
have to trade those things in for pickup trucks or get secure about
your masculinity.
</P>
<P>
   All Americans understand the guy-chick distinction, even if they
object to the word ``chick.'' Recently it's been rescued from the
overflowing dustbin of political incorrectness, but as my wife
says, ``I can use it but you can't.''
</P>
<P>
   Sure enough, many men, especially TV movie reviewers, chicken
out in mixed company and instead of calling the latest Meg Ryan
opus a ``chick movie,'' call it a ``date movie.''
</P>
<P>
   ``A date movie is a chick movie a guy takes a girl to when he
wants to get (rhymes with a Florida county),'' said my wife, who is
definitely not what you'd call a chick, at least if you're a guy
who values his front teeth.
</P>
<P>
   Still, she knows what's chick and what's guy. I asked her to
describe the difference between chick movies and guy movies.
</P>
<P>
   ``Guy movies have melting faces and lots of detonators,'' she
said. ``Chick movies have crying and phone calls.''
</P>
<P>
   There are exceptions to the rules, of course. My wife says that
if a movie has lots of detonators and Keanu Reeves, then it can be
a chick movie.
</P>
<P>
   But no amount of detonators and melting faces could make
anything by Julia Roberts and Hugh Grant a guy movie. Although,
maybe if they were melted and detonated. . . .
</P>
<P>
   The ultimate chick TV is Lifetime and daytime, while guy TV is
``The Man Show,'' the Hitler Channel _ I mean the History Channel _
and that one with all the airplanes.
</P>
<P>
   The chick computer is the iMac. It's Hello Kitty without a face.
The guy computer is whatever costs the most.
</P>
<P>
   The guy idea of a chick present is an ``outfit.'' The chick idea
of a guy present is something beige he'll never wear.
</P>
<P>
   The ideal chick weekend involves walks on the beach. A guy
weekend involves Laguna Seca.
</P>
<P>
   Chick music is all that stuff by women with names like Alanis,
Fiona and Jonatha, stuff I happen to like because I'm a sensitive
guy of the Joni generation. Guy music, according to my wife, is
stuff by Oasis or Bush. Never heard of them.
</P>
<P>
   Bush, the governor, I've heard of, and he's a guy politician
with both chick and guy appeal, unfortunately for Al Gore. The
ultimate chick politician, of course, is Hillary Rodham Clinton.
That is, she has chick appeal like Oprah and Martha, but the last
thing you'd ever call her is a chick.
</P>
<P>
   Not that we want to call any women ``chicks.'' We're talking
about a polar distinction in a society obsessed by gender roles and
the social construction of reality - to throw around a few chick
phrases.
</P>
<P>
   If anthropologist Claude Levi-Strauss did field work in modern
America, he wouldn't have written ``The Raw and the Cooked.'' He
would have written ``The Chick and the Guy.''
</P>
<P>
   Chick food and guy food are both sort of al dente. That's where
the resemblance ends. Even when it comes to pasta, meat sauce is
guy and pesto is chick.
</P>
<P>
   The ultimate chick food is Chinese chicken salad. The ultimate
guy food is meat. And the meat in Chinese chicken salad doesn't
count.
</P>
<P>
   Try this experiment sometime. The man orders the Chinese chicken
salad and the woman orders the meat, then see what happens.
</P>
<P>
   Real men can admit they like chick stuff. I'm a guy who likes
cosmos, white wine and Chinese chicken salad (well, with a side of
meat). I own an iMac and drive an SUV _ worse, a little Honda SUV.
</P>
<P>
   I've read ``Bridget Jones's Diary.'' The female clerk in the
bookstore said she'd never sold a copy to a man before. Did you
ever try to read Tom Clancy?
</P>
<P>
   I'll even watch Jane Austen movies on A&AMP;E, but during
commercials I'll be on the remote flipping to war footage on the
Hitler Channel.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Rob Morse is a columnist for the San Francisco Examiner, P.O.
Box 7260, San Francisco, CA 94120.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
