<SLUG> BC-CYC-ARMSTRONG0725-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Armstrong to begin whirlwind publicity tour of United States
 &HT;    By Suzanne Halliburton
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   PARIS _ Lance Armstrong spent only a few hours at his part-time
home in Nice, France, late Monday, leaving Paris a day after
clinching his second straight Tour de France championship.
</P>
<P>
   This morning he starts his whirlwind publicity tour of the
United States, flying to New York and then Los Angeles before
returning to France on Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Bill Stapleton, Armstrong's Austin-based attorney, said
Armstrong is scheduled to appear on ``Good Morning America'' and
``Live with Regis and Kathie Lee'' on Wednesday. There is a
possibility Armstrong will appear on other network talk shows, but
those interviews had not been set by Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
   Nike Inc., Armstrong's longtime sponsor, has set up a press
conference and book signing at Nike Town in Manhattan Wednesday
afternoon. A letter from President Clinton will be read to
Armstrong during the press conference.
</P>
<P>
   On Thursday, Armstrong will fly to Los Angeles. He is scheduled
to appear on the ``Tonight Show'' Thursday. There also will be a
party thrown in his honor at a home in Beverly Hills. The mansion
will be lighted in yellow to commemorate Armstrong's second
straight Tour championship.
</P>
<P>
   Friday, Armstrong returns to Nice to prepare for the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
   Last year, Armstrong was able to return to Austin in August
after his Tour victory. But because of the Olympics in Sydney in
September, Armstrong will not return home until early October.
</P>
<P>
   With his win in the Tour time trial on Friday, Armstrong has
emerged as the leading contender for the gold medal in the Olympic
time trial on Sept. 30. The Olympic time trial course and the one
Armstrong rode from Freiburg, Germany, to Mulhouse, France, are
very similar.
</P>
<P>
   To prepare for the Olympics, Armstrong will compete in two races
in Spain _ the San Sebastian and the Tour of Borgos. He also will
compete in the World Cup at Zurich, Switzerland. He then will
travel to Australia in mid-September.
</P>
<P>
   You may contact Suzanne Halliburton at
shalliburton(at)statesman.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
