<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-RONWRONG _ Jane O'Boyle did what any of us could have done
with a particle of imagination and an ounce of follow-through: She
compiled Wrong! (Plume, $11.95), a collection of the biggest
bonehead predictions, pronouncements and decisions ever made, and
offered them to the public in an 88-page, soft-cover book. The
result is _ well, two kinds of reading satisfaction. The first is
relief in knowing that it wasn't you who committed the big-time
gaffe. The second is the perverse pride of authorship when you know
that your own stupidity has surpassed
</P>
<P>
   the examples given. (Wiggins, Palm Beach Post) DORMROOMS _ Away
from home, on your own, without so much as a clue. Take this
advice, make your place nice and banish the dorm room blues.
(Graulich, Palm Beach Post)PRACTICAL-MAN _ The practical man lit up
last week. When he heard the tobacco verdict. No, he has nothing
against tobacco companies. In fact, the practical man puts them on
par with coffee growers and Scotch distillers, for he knows the
tasty truth about cigarettes: They're yummy. (Practical Man, Palm
Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   CONSUMERQ&AMP;A _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Consumer Q&AMP;A. (Greig, Austin
American-Statesman) (l, a) MOVED.
</P>
