   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in the ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   FRANCE-FUGITIVE (Undated) _ French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin
has signed extradition papers ordering that fugitive and convicted
murderer Ira Einhorn be returned to Pennsylvania, Philadelphia
officials said. By Francis X. Clines.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in the ``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   HMOS-MEDICARE (Washington) _ More than 933,600 elderly and
disabled people will soon be dropped by health maintenance
organizations leaving the Medicare program, the Clinton
administration said Monday. The number, which is substantially
greater than estimates last month by the HMO industry, underlines
the turbulence and instability of the market in which Medicare
beneficiaries seek private health insurance. By Robert Pear.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL GENERAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-RAPE-DNA (Austin) _ Prosecutors in Texas agreed Monday to
ask for a pardon for a man sentenced to 99 years for rape. DNA
evidence exonerated him but the state's highest court had dismissed
the evidence. By Jim Yardley.
</P>
<P>
   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``p'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   GA-MILLER (Atlanta) _ Roy Barnes of Georgia on Monday appointed
former Gov. Zell Miller to fill the Senate seat left vacant by the
death of Paul Coverdell. By Kevin Sack.
</P>
</TEXT>
