</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup chopped green pepper &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup carrot slices &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup mayonnaise &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon onion powder &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/8 teaspoon pepper &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 (8-ounce) can crushed OR cubed pineapple, drained &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Prepare rice according to package directions. Chill. Combine
with all remaining ingredients; mix lightly. Chill. Serve with
bread, rolls or garlic toast. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CURRY CHICKEN SALAD &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Shared by Elinor Koby, Valencia) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 cups mayonnaise &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons lemon juice &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 1/2 tablespoons soy sauce &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 rounded tablespoon curry powder &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon onion juice &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon chopped chutney &QL;
</P>
<P>
   3 cups diced, cooked chicken &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 cups chopped celery &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 (6-ounce) can water chestnuts, drained and sliced &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 cups seedless white grapes &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 (20-ounce) can pineapple chunks, well drained &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup slivered almonds, toasted &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, soy sauce, curry powder, onion
juice and chutney. Toss with remaining ingredients except almonds.
Refrigerate overnight. Sprinkle with almonds. Serve with banana
bread. Makes 8 servings. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
