   1 (16-ounce) can sauerkraut, well drained &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 cups fresh bean sprouts, rinsed and drained &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup sliced celery &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup finely chopped onion &QL;
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons finely chopped green pepper &QL;
</P>
<P>
   1 (2-ounce) jar pimento, drained and chopped &QL;
</P>
<P>
   In a screw-top jar, for dressing, combine sugar, vinegar and
oil. Cover and shake to dissolve sugar.
</P>
<P>
   Pour over remaining ingredients; tossing to coat. Cover and
refrigerate overnight. Serve on lettuce-lined plates. Makes 6 to 8
servings.
