<P>
   CONFEDERATE (Mesa, Ariz.) - The nationwide Confederate Air
Force, which has a museum in Mesa, is attempting to change its name
because of the stigma now connected with the word ``confederate.''
Corporations have begun cutting back on donations because of the
name. Actually, the group of about 9,000 members has nothing to do
with the Civil War but is dedicated to preserving old military
aircraft. The group was founded in the mid 1950s and acquired the
name as sort of a joke. It will probably take at least two years
for a name change because bylaws require a countrywide election,
with 75 percent support for a name change. By BETTY BEARD. Story
will move in the ``A'' category.
</P>
</TEXT>
