<P>
   MIDEAST-TALKS (Thurmont, Md.) _ In its 14th day, the Camp David
peace negotiations intensify as President Clinton plunges into the
nitty-gritty of issue-by-issue deliberations. After meeting until
almost dawn with Israeli and Palestinian negotiators, he then
oversaw a day and night of what officials said quietly was the
exercise of drafting the skeleton of an agreement. The White House,
which is overseeing a news blackout on the sensitive talks, would
not confirm that a document was being drafted. By Deborah Sontag.
(Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.) 1,400 words.
