Texas's toxic release levels actually declined by 15 percent from
1995 to 1997.
</P>
<P>
   The largest problem is the dangerous amount of nitrogen oxide
(which mixes with vehicle-exhaust gas to create ozone, and then
smog) coughed out by the state's industrial plants.
</P>
<P>
   Last year, when Houston surpassed Los Angeles as the country's
