   BANKS ARE SLOW TO MOVE ONLINE, BUT SO ARE THEIR CUSTOMERS
</P>
<P>
   BC-ECOM-ONLINE-BANKING-NYTSF _ Unlike online stock trading,
online banking has not, so far, taken off. Why? ``The advent of
Net-only banks seems so exciting,'' says Bruce Zimmerman, a senior
vice president of Chase Manhattan Bank. ``But the reality is, there
aren't many customers who want to do everything only over the Net.
That's why you've seen that Net-only models haven't been
successful.'' By Patrick McGeehan. WITH ILLUSTRATION.
</P>
