<P>
   RUSSIA-COLDWATER _ MOSCOW _ Russians look forward to summer with
a mixture of joy and despair, for as soon as warm weather hits this
country, the hot water gets turned off. In Moscow families lose
their hot water for up to a month at a time, thanks to a system
that is a holdover to the Soviet-era central hot water system. You
know your turn has come by a simple, handwritten note by the front
door. This prompts a flurry of new conversation from everyone you
meet on the street _ instead of complaining of the cold weather,
people complain about cold showers. (Coker, Cox News Service). WITH
PHOTO.
</P>
